<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Backward1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Backward,</orth> adv. toward the back, back: <cit><quote>b. she pushed him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 41" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and b. drew the heavenly moisture,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 41" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 41</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. ven 41" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 41</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.214" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 214</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.214" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 214</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.5.3" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 5, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 2, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 42</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 5, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.206" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 206</bibl>. Figuratively == from the wrong end, perversely: <cit><quote>she would spell him b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 61</bibl></cit>, i. e. she would make vices of his virtues; cf. <emph>backwardly.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>